/> To which I would say, &#8220;what&#8217;s the point in accumulating gold if you&#8217;re going to blow up the financial system you plan to profit in?&#8221;</p><p>As this writer suggests, China would prefer a gradual shift, but if they&#8217;re naive enoughto think the US will sit back and let it happen, even slowly,  they have some surprises coming.<br
/> If any country wants to be the foremost superpower,  they shoulr expect to be required to own the foremost military to back up their position. Thinking you can become the most powerful nation strictly by trade is a mistake. The great civilizations of the past found this out when their military might waned, even while their trade was still strong. They were soon cut down by stronger nations, marauding bands, or atrophy of their colonies due to being too weak to protect them.</p><p>China had best consider this lesson from history.</p></div></div><ul
